column4:
Communication Ethics

In this course, I teach critical examination of ethical issues related to communication, information, and the media. Freedoms and responsibilities. Consideration of such issues as: privacy, confidentiality, censorship, deception, propaganda, accuracy, fairness, intellectual property rights, conflicts of interest, obscenity and pornography, civility and offensive speech. Classical and contemporary philosophers.

Visit the course

Quixote is an adjunct professor of philosophy, editor, digital media archivist and musician situated in Brooklyn, NY. He holds a Bachelors in Philosophy from Brooklyn College and is pursuing his MA in Liberal Studies at the CUNY Graduate Center.
